  What can I say on this one!  SCAN obviously could use a few more
bells and whistles; on the other hand, what's done works ok.  As time
goes on I hope to add various enhancements here and there...
such as a low resolution option, faster screen routines, and more
thorough documentation.
  SCAN operation is fairly straightforward:  Locate a Degas
BL2 file on the same disk as SCAN.BAS (a test file is supplied in
SCAN.ARC).  Run the program.  Voila.  Simple as that.
  Note the GEMDOS SETDTA($1A) and SFIRST($4E) require "long"
words as parameters.  Information on BASEPAGE, page 249, the GFA
manual, is helpful.  Don't forget, though, an L: should 
precede the "BASEPAGE+128."
  As always, comments and suggestions most welcome.
  Have fun and hack on!

Greg Sheppard
